The paper discusses the ability of neural networks to serve as generative models for complicated types of data such as images and texts, which is a topic closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Specifically, the paper focuses on the expressivity of multilayer neural networks and their ability to approximate probability distributions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, since the paper mentions images, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, since the paper discusses the theoretical understanding of neural networks, cs.SI (Systems and Control) is another possible sub-category.
